<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <meta name="theme-color" content="#0a0c0e">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Geist:wght@400;500;600;700;800&family=Geist+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/marketing.css">
  </head>
  <body>
    @include('site-nav')

    <main>
      <nav class="shell subnav" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span>
        <a href="/#features">Features</a><span class="sep">/</span>
        <span>Sources and referrers</span>
      </nav>

      <section class="feat-hero shell">
        <span class="kicker">Acquisition</span>
        <h1>Know exactly where your traffic comes from.</h1>
        <p>Every referrer is classified on arrival, so search, social, direct, and campaign traffic separate at a glance. UTM tags flow straight into the report.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a class="btn primary" href="/dashboard">See a live dashboard</a>
          <a class="btn ghost" href="/#install">Get your script tag</a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="reveal section shell" aria-label="Sources and referrers preview">
        <div class="panel" style="max-width: 640px">
          <div class="panel-head"><span class="chart-cap">Traffic by channel</span><span class="panel-tag">Sample data</span></div>
          <div class="bar-row">
            <span class="bar-label">Search</span>
            <span class="bar-track"><span class="bar-fill" style="width: 100%"></span></span>
            <span class="bar-value">42%</span>
          </div>
          <div class="bar-row">
            <span class="bar-label">Direct</span>
            <span class="bar-track"><span class="bar-fill" style="width: 57%"></span></span>
            <span class="bar-value">24%</span>
          </div>
          <div class="bar-row">
            <span class="bar-label">Social</span>
            <span class="bar-track"><span class="bar-fill" style="width: 45%"></span></span>
            <span class="bar-value">19%</span>
          </div>
          <div class="bar-row">
            <span class="bar-label">Referral</span>
            <span class="bar-track"><span class="bar-fill" style="width: 36%"></span></span>
            <span class="bar-value">15%</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="reveal section shell" aria-labelledby="how-heading">
        <div class="section-head">
          <h2 id="how-heading" class="section-title">How it works</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="flow">
          <div class="flow-step">
            <span class="flow-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h3>The referrer arrives with the hit</h3>
              <p>The beacon carries the document referrer and any UTM parameters on the landing URL.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flow-step">
            <span class="flow-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h3>Channels are classified</h3>
              <p>Known search engines, social networks, and referrers are matched to a channel, and the rest fall into direct or referral.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flow-step">
            <span class="flow-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h3>Campaigns stay attached</h3>
              <p>utm_source, utm_medium, and utm_campaign are kept with the session so a campaign ties to its outcomes.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="reveal section shell" aria-label="What you get">
        <div class="metrics">
          <div class="metric">
            <div class="m-value">Automatic</div>
            <div class="m-label">Search, social, direct, and referral split without any manual tagging.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="metric">
            <div class="m-value">UTM native</div>
            <div class="m-label">Campaign parameters are first-class, not an afterthought bolted on later.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="metric">
            <div class="m-value">Clean</div>
            <div class="m-label">Self-referrals and common spam referrers are filtered so the report stays honest.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="reveal section shell" aria-labelledby="related-heading">
        <div class="section-head">
          <h2 id="related-heading" class="section-title">Pairs well with</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="related">
          <a href="/features/goals">
            <div class="r-name">Goals and campaigns</div>
            <div class="r-desc">Connect a channel to the conversions it drives.</div>
          </a>
          <a href="/features/metrics">
            <div class="r-name">Pageviews and sessions</div>
            <div class="r-desc">See how each channel sessions behave.</div>
          </a>
          <a href="/features/geography">
            <div class="r-name">Geography and devices</div>
            <div class="r-desc">Break a channel down by country and device.</div>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="reveal section shell" aria-label="Get started">
        <div class="cta-band">
          <h2>Your numbers. Your visitors' privacy. Both intact.</h2>
          <div class="cta-actions">
            <a class="btn primary" href="/#install">Get your script tag</a>
            <a class="btn ghost" href="/dashboard">See a live dashboard</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="footer shell">
      <div class="footer-bottom" style="border-top: none">
        <a class="brand" href="/" aria-label="ghostanalytics home">
          <span class="brand-mark">g</span>
          <span class="brand-name">ghostanalytics</span>
        </a>
        <span>No cookies. No personal data. Powered by Stacks and PostgreSQL.</span>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
